        "timestamp": "2020-08-13 08:08:48.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> (1 comment)\n\ntechnically I think it is not a problem\nwe can add a sys-requirements.txt and use it on build step\nBUT how can we guarantee that we do not introduce a GPLv3 lib in this case..(e.g bash)\nthe goal of the baseline is to offer a GPLv3 free python docker\n\nso my view then will be to disable the ONBOARD option\nbaseline will be OK\nProject could install whatever they want but the responsibility will be on project side\nI will amend the patch in this direction",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
